<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>DoD Banner Library &mdash; Release Notes</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --primary:        #1b3a6b;
      --primary-light:  #e8edf5;
      --success-border: #c3e6c3;
      --warning-border: #fde7a0;
      --error-border:   #f3c6c7;
      --bg:             #f3f2f1;
      --surface:        #ffffff;
      --border:         #edebe9;
      --text:           #323130;
      --text-secondary: #605e5c;
      --text-disabled:  #a19f9d;
      --radius:         4px;
      --shadow:         0 1.6px 3.6px rgba(0,0,0,.13), 0 .3px .9px rgba(0,0,0,.11);
    }
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    body { font-family: 'Segoe UI', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text); background: var(--bg); min-height: 100vh; }
    .app-header { background: var(--primary); color: #fff; padding: 18px 32px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 16px; }
    .app-header-icon { width: 40px; height: 40px; background: rgba(255,255,255,.18); border-radius: var(--radius); display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 22px; flex-shrink: 0; }
    .app-header h1 { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; }
    .app-header p  { font-size: 12px; opacity: .85; margin-top: 2px; }
    .back-link { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; margin: 20px 32px 0; background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); text-decoration: none; box-shadow: var(--shadow); }
    .back-link:hover { color: var(--primary); background: var(--primary-light); }
    .main { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 24px 32px 48px; }
    .version-block { margin-bottom: 32px; }
    .version-header { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 16px; padding-bottom: 10px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border); margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .version-tag { font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); font-family: 'Cascadia Code','Consolas',monospace; }
    .version-date { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .version-badge { display: inline-block; padding: 2px 10px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; background: var(--success-border); color: #0e5a0e; margin-left: auto; }
    .change-group { margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .change-group-title { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .06em; color: var(--text-disabled); margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .change-list { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
    .change-item { display: flex; gap: 12px; align-items: flex-start; background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 10px 14px; box-shadow: var(--shadow); font-size: 13px; }
    .change-pill { flex-shrink: 0; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 1px; }
    .pill-new    { background: #dce9f8; color: #004578; }
    .pill-remove { background: var(--error-border); color: #6b0c0e; }
    .change-text { color: var(--text-secondary); flex: 1; }
    .change-text strong { color: var(--text); }
    code { font-family: 'Cascadia Code','Consolas',monospace; font-size: 12px; background: var(--bg); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 3px; padding: 1px 5px; color: #005a9e; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="app-header">
  <div class="app-header-icon">&#x1F4CB;</div>
  <div>
    <h1>DoD Banner Library</h1>
    <p>Release Notes</p>
  </div>
</div>

<a class="back-link" href="dodbl_docs">&larr; Documentation</a>

<div class="main">

  <div class="version-block">
    <div class="version-header">
      <span class="version-tag" style="color:var(--text-disabled)">v1.3.0</span>
      <span class="version-date" style="color:var(--text-disabled)">Planned</span>
    </div>
    <div class="change-group">
      <div class="change-group-title">Planned</div>
      <ul class="change-list">
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Dataverse consent audit table</strong> &mdash; <code>dodbl_consent_record</code> with columns: <code>dodbl_systemuser</code> (Lookup), <code>dodbl_acknowledgedon</code>, <code>dodbl_expirydate</code>, <code>dodbl_consenttype</code>, <code>dodbl_consenttext</code>, <code>dodbl_isactive</code>. Table-level auditing enabled.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Security role</strong> &mdash; <code>DoD Banner &mdash; Consent Write</code> for granting consent record create access to Authenticated Users in Power Pages.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>PCF cookie hardening</strong> &mdash; Rename consent cookie from <code>Accepted</code> to <code>dodbl_Accepted</code> to prevent domain-level collision; add <code>Secure</code> flag for GCC High HTTPS environments.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="version-block">
    <div class="version-header">
      <span class="version-tag">v1.2.0</span>
      <span class="version-date">2026-07-24</span>
      <span class="version-badge">Latest</span>
    </div>
    <div class="change-group">
      <div class="change-group-title">New</div>
      <ul class="change-list">
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>showConsent PCF property</strong> &mdash; New <code>showConsent</code> (TwoOptions) input property on <code>DodBannerControl</code>. Decouples the DoD system-use notification consent modal from <code>bannerType</code>. Set <code>showConsent = true</code> to show the consent modal without a classification bar. Legacy <code>bannerType = "DoD"</code> continues to work.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>CSS injection for Canvas Apps</strong> &mdash; PCF now injects all modal styles directly into <code>document.head</code> (<code>&lt;style data-dodbl-pcf-styles&gt;</code>) at runtime. Canvas Apps and Custom Pages do not load <code>dodbl_bannercore.css</code>, so the bundle is now fully self-contained. Idempotent &mdash; safe across multiple <code>updateView</code> calls.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>DoD placeholder indicator</strong> &mdash; When <code>showConsent = true</code> and no classification bar is configured, the PCF control renders a navy dashed &ldquo;&#x26A0; DoD Consent&rdquo; placeholder so the control is visible in the Canvas App editor. At runtime the full modal and dark overlay appear.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Dark overlay</strong> &mdash; Semi-transparent full-viewport overlay (<code>rgba(0,0,0,0.45)</code>) blocks interaction with the app until the user acknowledges. Renders beneath the modal at <code>z-index: 9997</code>.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="change-group">
      <div class="change-group-title">Removed</div>
      <ul class="change-list">
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-remove">REMOVED</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Close button (&#x00D7;) removed from PCF modal</strong> &mdash; The <code>#closeCookieConsent</code> dismiss-without-acknowledging button has been removed. Users must click <strong>I Acknowledge</strong> to dismiss the DoD system-use notification. This satisfies the DoD requirement for affirmative acknowledgement.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="change-group">
      <div class="change-group-title">Fixed</div>
      <ul class="change-list">
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">FIX</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Modal display flash</strong> &mdash; Modal no longer briefly flashes visible before the 800&thinsp;ms delay. The element starts as <code>display:none</code> and is revealed immediately before <code>fadeIn</code> begins.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">FIX</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Modal contrast and spacing</strong> &mdash; Increased padding (<code>24px 28px</code>), added border (<code>2px solid #555</code>), and deepened box-shadow for legibility on all background colors.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="version-block">
    <div class="version-header">
      <span class="version-tag">v1.1.0</span>
      <span class="version-date">2026-07-23</span>
    </div>
    <div class="change-group">
      <div class="change-group-title">New</div>
      <ul class="change-list">
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>dodbl_dodbanner &mdash; MDA form OnLoad script</strong> &mdash; Reads six <code>dodbl_</code> environment variables via <code>Xrm.WebApi</code>. Handler: <code>DoDBannerLibrary.DodBanner.onFormLoad</code>. No PCF or Premium license required.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Consent via <code>Xrm.App.addGlobalNotification</code></strong> &mdash; DoD system-use notification renders as a native UCI yellow warning bar with &ldquo;I Acknowledge&rdquo; action. Replaces the DOM-injected modal. Persists across form navigation. Requires no <code>window.top</code> access.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>dodbl_ShowConsentBanner</strong> env var (Boolean) &mdash; Decouples consent from the classification bar. Set to <code>yes</code> to show the DoD system-use notification independently of <code>dodbl_BannerType</code>.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>dodbl_BannerPosition</strong> env var (String) &mdash; Controls classification bar placement: <code>Bottom</code> (default), <code>Top</code>, or <code>Both</code>. Top placement shifts the MDA global nav header down 28&thinsp;px to avoid overlap.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Environment variables (6 total)</strong> &mdash; <code>dodbl_BannerEnabled</code>, <code>dodbl_BannerType</code>, <code>dodbl_DoDConsentText</code>, <code>dodbl_ConsentExpiryDays</code>, <code>dodbl_ShowConsentBanner</code>, <code>dodbl_BannerPosition</code>.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>DodBannerControl PCF for Canvas Apps</strong> &mdash; PCF field control providing consent modal and classification bar for Canvas Apps. Requires Power Apps Premium or Managed Environment. Properties: <code>bannerEnabled</code>, <code>bannerType</code>, <code>consentExpiryDays</code>, <code>consentText</code>.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>dodbl_webtemplatesource</strong> &mdash; Power Pages Web Template source page with step-by-step Liquid setup instructions.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>DoD Banner Library Management app</strong> &mdash; Model-driven app providing in-environment access to documentation, release notes, and web template source from the app switcher.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="version-block">
    <div class="version-header">
      <span class="version-tag">v1.2.0</span>
      <span class="version-date">2026-07-24</span>
      <span class="version-badge">Latest</span>
    </div>
    <div class="change-group">
      <div class="change-group-title">New</div>
      <ul class="change-list">
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>showConsent PCF property</strong> &mdash; New <code>showConsent</code> (TwoOptions) input property on <code>DodBannerControl</code>. Decouples the DoD system-use notification consent modal from <code>bannerType</code>. Set <code>showConsent = true</code> to show the consent modal without a classification bar. Legacy <code>bannerType = "DoD"</code> continues to work.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>CSS injection for Canvas Apps</strong> &mdash; PCF now injects all modal styles directly into <code>document.head</code> (<code>&lt;style data-dodbl-pcf-styles&gt;</code>) at runtime. Canvas Apps and Custom Pages do not load <code>dodbl_bannercore.css</code>, so the bundle is now fully self-contained. Idempotent &mdash; safe across multiple <code>updateView</code> calls.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>DoD placeholder indicator</strong> &mdash; When <code>showConsent = true</code> and no classification bar is configured, the PCF control renders a navy dashed &ldquo;&#x26A0; DoD Consent&rdquo; placeholder so the control is visible in the Canvas App editor. At runtime the full modal and dark overlay appear.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Dark overlay</strong> &mdash; Semi-transparent full-viewport overlay (<code>rgba(0,0,0,0.45)</code>) blocks interaction with the app until the user acknowledges. Renders beneath the modal at <code>z-index: 9997</code>.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="change-group">
      <div class="change-group-title">Removed</div>
      <ul class="change-list">
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-remove">REMOVED</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Close button (&#x00D7;) removed from PCF modal</strong> &mdash; The <code>#closeCookieConsent</code> dismiss-without-acknowledging button has been removed. Users must click <strong>I Acknowledge</strong> to dismiss the DoD system-use notification. This satisfies the DoD requirement for affirmative acknowledgement.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="change-group">
      <div class="change-group-title">Fixed</div>
      <ul class="change-list">
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">FIX</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Modal display flash</strong> &mdash; Modal no longer briefly flashes visible before the 800&thinsp;ms delay. The element starts as <code>display:none</code> and is revealed immediately before <code>fadeIn</code> begins.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">FIX</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Modal contrast and spacing</strong> &mdash; Increased padding (<code>24px 28px</code>), added border (<code>2px solid #555</code>), and deepened box-shadow for legibility on all background colors.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="version-block">
    <div class="version-header">
      <span class="version-tag">v1.0.0</span>
      <span class="version-date">2026-07-22</span>
    </div>
    <div class="change-group">
      <div class="change-group-title">New</div>
      <ul class="change-list">
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>banner-core.css</strong> &mdash; shared stylesheet combining DoD consent modal responsive layout (3 breakpoints) and CUI classification mark color rules for all five levels.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>dod-consent-banner.html</strong> &mdash; DoD system-use notification consent modal. Vanilla JavaScript, no external dependencies. GCC High / IL4/IL5 safe.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>cui-consent-banner.html</strong> &mdash; CUI classification mark banner fragment. CSS-only, no JavaScript required. Supports top (<code>.classification-banner</code>) and bottom (<code>.classification-banner-bot</code>) placement via <code>data-classification</code> attribute.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Solution packaging</strong> &mdash; all assets packaged as a managed Power Platform solution (<code>dod_banner_library</code>) with publisher prefix <code>dodbl</code>. Supports GCC High tenant import.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-new">NEW</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Documentation web resources</strong> &mdash; <code>dodbl_docs</code> and <code>dodbl_release-notes</code> included in the solution for in-environment reference.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="change-group">
      <div class="change-group-title">Removed</div>
      <ul class="change-list">
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-remove">REMOVED</span><span class="change-text"><strong>jQuery CDN dependency</strong> &mdash; the <code>jquery-3.7.1.js</code> CDN script tag was removed from the consent banner. All jQuery calls replaced with vanilla JavaScript equivalents. No behavior change for end users.</span></li>
        <li class="change-item"><span class="change-pill pill-remove">REMOVED</span><span class="change-text"><strong>Inline <code>&lt;style&gt;</code> blocks</strong> &mdash; CSS extracted from both HTML files and consolidated into <code>banner-core.css</code> to enable a single web resource upload for all platforms.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>
</body>
</html>